@node tap "What is a TAP image?"

What is a TAP image?

TAP images are images of c64 tapes.

These images are supported by the currently best c64 emulators on 
IBM compatible PC's which are CCS64 and VICE.

While the old tape format from C64S (T64) just stored the files,
TAP contains the "true" data stored on a tape as it is seen by a
c64. This means that these images just contain a lot of signal
lengths and is as low-level as it should be to fully emulate c64
tapes. (You can store your tape originals and load them with CCS!)

@endnode
